<item>
            <title>[JDK-8314220] Configurable InlineCacheBuffer size</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8314220</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>InlineCacheBuffer size is currently hardcoded to 10K.&lt;br/&gt;
This can lead to multiple ICBufferFull safepoints for InlineCacheBuffer cleanup and possible performance degradation.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It may be useful to make the size configurable with command line option for performance experiments with ICBufferFull safepoints frequency.</description>
