                            <comment id="14654383" author="evergizova" created="Mon, 4 Mar 2024 11:22:29 -0800"  >[~goetz] Some applications running on 11u have performance problems due to excess ICBufferFull safepoints.&lt;br/&gt;
This change allows to avoid the problem. It is simple and low risk and it does not change the current behavior if InlineCacheBufferSize is set to default value.</comment>
                            <comment id="14654258" author="goetz" created="Mon, 4 Mar 2024 03:57:00 -0800"  >[~katya] Why is this needed in 11u?  11u is a stable release.</comment>
                            <comment id="14653877" author="evergizova" created="Fri, 1 Mar 2024 04:41:06 -0800"  >Fix Request [11u]&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;d like to backport it to 11u. It allows to configure IC buffer size to avoid multiple ICBufferFull safepoints and possible performance degradation.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
17u patch applies almost cleanly except for:&lt;br/&gt;
- minor context difference in icBuffer.cpp&lt;br/&gt;
- different method for experimental flag declaration in globals.hpp (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8243208&quot; title=&quot;Clean up JVMFlag implementation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8243208&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8243208&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is not in 11u)&lt;br/&gt;
The changes reapplied manually.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The change is simple and low risk, it does not change the current behavior if InlineCacheBufferSize is set to its default value.</comment>
